The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Dantewada suspects held
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Dantewada suspects held
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Raipur, May 24: Six members of a militia that allegedly helped Maoists plot and execute last months massacre of 75 CRPF jawans in Dantewada were arrested last night.        
	The six included a self-styled commander of the Jan Militia who told police that members of his outfit had handed over to the rebels a CRPF wireless set the personnel lost a day before the April 6 ambush. The gadget helped the rebels intercept the forces messages and lay the trap.        
	Dantewada SP Amresh Mishra said the militia commander, Barsa Lakhma, and five others  Oyam Hidma, Podiyami Hidma, Kawasi Budra, Oya Ganga and Dura Joga  were not hardcore members of the CPI (Maoist) but had played a key role in the attack.        
	Lakhma did not have much information on the hierarchy or the strategies and operation of the Maoists. He reported to Papa Rao, the Maoists area commander, Mishra said.         
	During interrogation, Lakhma revealed that some 300 rebels had ambushed the jawans, the police said. Of them, 190 were Maoists from Company Number 8 of the CPI (Maoist), the rest militia members.                                                                                                                                                           
